HEADWORD: Streptoneura
<hw>Strep`to*neu"ra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <?/ curved + <?/ a sinew.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An
extensive division of gastropod Mollusca in which the loop or visceral
nerves is twisted, and the sexes separate. It is nearly to equivalent to
Prosobranchiata.</def>⟦br⟧
